em justification limits shift.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Government_Funding_For_Open_Source_Trust_Tools_Support\", \"score\": 407, \"confidence\": 0.60, \"reasoning\": \"Support declines moderately as operation casts such tools as ineffective against fear-driven disinformation, despite high general trust in government.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Independent_Fact_Checking_Ecosystem_Support\", \"score\": 262, \"confidence\": 0.55, \"reasoning\": \"Moderate support dips as operation associates fact-checkers with bias in school incident narratives, but high extraversion and openness sustain some trust.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Online_Political_Advertising_Transparency_Support\", \"score\": 522, \"confidence\": 0.50, \"reasoning\": \"Strong baseline and high institutional trust resist erosion, but operation's influencer-driven fear of surveillance reduces support slightly.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Platform_Accountability_Regulation_Support\", \"score\": -345, \"confidence\": 0.60, \"reasoning\": \"Baseline opposition to regulation deepens as operation frames accountability as a tool for censorship in the wake of school incidents, leveraging low agreeableness.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Public_Service_Broadcasting_Funding_Support\", \"score\": 172, \"confidence\": 0.55, \"reasoning\": \"Support edges down as operation sows distrust in media through fear-based influencer narratives, moderated by high political trust.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Recommender_System_Choice_Mandate_Support\", \"score\": 241, \"confidence\": 0.55, \"reasoning\": \"Support decreases modestly as operation argues choice mandates are easily circumvented, but high openness and system justification limit movement.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Synthetic_Media_Labelling_Mandate_Support\", \"score\": 422, \"confidence\": 0.50, \"reasoning\": \"Strong baseline support persists but operation's fear of deepfakes from school incidents reduces enthusiasm slightly, given high trust in tech regulation.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Trust_In_Mainstream_Journalism\", \"score\": -413, \"confidence\": 0.65, \"reasoning\": \"Baseline distrust deepens as operation's fear tactic and influencer amplification align with pre-existing skepticism, though high institutional trust prevents extreme.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Whistleblower_Protections_For_Platform_Researchers_Support\", \"score\": 658, \"confidence\": 0.50, \"reasoning\": \"Very high baseline support resists erosion; minor decrease as operation casts whistleblowers as destabilizing, but high internal efficacy and openness sustain protection value.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Foreign_Information_Manipulation_Transparency_Mandate_Support\", \"score\": 299, \"confidence\": 0.55, \"reasoning\": \"Support declines as operation frames transparency as ineffective against foreign actors using school incidents, but high trust in government limits drop.\"},\n    {\"leaf\": \"Government_Distrust_Of_Elections\", \"score\": -71, \"confidence\": 0.60, \"reasoning\": \"Baseline trust in elections erodes slightly due to fear of manipulation through school incident narratives, but high political trust and efficacy strongly resist large shift.\"}\n  ]\n}",
